parameters: Is it just a decoration or something more?
Maybe I should ask \C[20]Grandpa Ek\c[0] about it...
Looks like it’s holding together now...
Still got that ancient vibe to it, though.
I doubt any monster’s walking through again.

The Ascendant Grounds don’t appear for the unready.
But for you—I'll open the path.
The forest’s quieter at night... less eyes, more focus.
You here to train—or just talk?
Could use a spar to shake off the day.
Hey... I didn’t expect anyone else out here.
I came from that path over there.
That path hasn’t opened for years.
You ever notice how everything hits different under moonlight?
Quieter. Colder. Still kinda peaceful, though.
That peace? That’s what we fight for. Not glory. Not pride.
These stones remember pain. Blood. Sacrifice.
A lot. Too much. I trained here when I was your age.
Left some of my rage in that corner over there.
The Ascendant Grounds don’t appear for the unready.
But for you—I'll open the path.

You really don’t take nights off, huh?
You caught me last time, didn’t you?
Might as well get used to it.
And I didn’t say stop watching.
Then I’ll take that as permission to admire greatness.
and I’ll start making you do planks until sunrise.
You’re the one who dragged me into this world—
Wanna join? It’s not all pain and sweat.
Alright, I’m game. Show me what you’ve got.
Didn’t have enough with stonework, huh?
Don’t mind me. I’m just here for the ride.
You really treat me like your favorite training mat.
Last time you twitched like I shocked you.
It’s kind of cute. Like it’s asking for attention.
If you can’t hold a plank while I do this,
how are you gonna survive in a real fight?
Guess that part of you’s always eager.
Let’s see how long you can really last this time.
Don’t you dare give up now.
When you reach the timer... then I’ll let you finish.
I think I just saw the gods...
I’m still sore from earlier—I’d just slow you down.
(She said she trains out here at night...
Guess I’ll check in—quietly this time.)
I swear I wasn’t trying to catch you training half-naked again.
You did watch me half-naked last time.
No eyes. No noise. Just me, the moon, and my thoughts.
Only because I didn’t know if I was about to die or...
But if you’re going to flirt, at least stretch first.
Man, this place is a maze.
At least it’s chill and relaxing.
Kinda hope I can find my way back...
I heard something! I didn’t know you were—
You’re lucky I don’t make you spar me for this.
I train out here most nights.
Helps me think. Helps me feel like... maybe I’m catching up.
No matter how much I train, I can’t match him.
It’s like I’m chasing a ghost.
And I don’t know if I’ll ever catch him.
(This isn’t the world I used to know anymore.
Maybe... there’s something more to all this.)
You weren’t supposed to see this.
I’m supposed to be stronger than this!
But the fact that you keep pushing?
I wouldn’t say it if I didn’t.
You want to break his shadow? Smash through it.
Heh... careful, \n[1]. You’re sounding like him.
Then take that energy and fight back.
Why do you have to see me like this—
Half-trained, half-dressed, and half of what I should be?
Because maybe that’s when you’re most real.
Before I decide to spar you anyway.
That was her fighting to believe in herself.
And I think... she’s starting to win.)

(I swear it’s not stalking—just... studying form. Right?)
You’ve got a habit of showing up at night when I’m alone.
or your timing just really sucks.
I swear, this time I was just—uh...
Relax. I was waiting for you.
There’s somewhere I want to go—and you’re coming with me.
I came here often with Grandpa.
It’s where he taught me to hold my ground...
We once fought off a pack of forest beasts together...
I wasn’t strong then. I mostly watched.
I’d be the one protecting others.
Now I wonder if I’ll ever be enough.
Hey... why’s it so quiet all of a sudden...?
It’s just a goblin—why so serious?
and they usually come in packs!
It looks small—but it’s insanely dense.)
Come on—let’s get out of here.
I’m no match for this thing!)
Tch. There’s no end to them!
(If I just had a little more...)
The earth bends not to strength alone, child.
It listens to the heart that dares to protect.
You have that heart. Trust it.
...Maybe you’re not alone in this after all.
My whole body’s yelling at me.
\C[20]Grandpa Ek\c[0] and our friend had to carry us back like broken weapons.
I’ve never felt that much power—or fear—all at once.)
(Wasn’t I supposed to tell Ek about something?)
The monument or whatever it’s called at Valor Grounds.)
(I should check it in the morning.)
*Maleena’s stance deepens, her breath steady and rooted.
it’s the earth itself standing guard.*

Night’s quiet—good time to work the body without distractions.
It still feels strange... moving with this power.
Like the earth listens before I even speak.
It’s not. But I want it to be... someday.
\C[20]Grandpa Ek\c[0] hasn’t said it, but I think he’s proud.
That’s a big deal coming from him.
Now we just have to live up to it.
My stance feels off with this new strength.
Too much force, not enough control.
You want to spar slower? Test the rhythm?
Yeah. Let’s figure it out — together.
No matter how much I train...
I still feel like I’m chasing a shadow.
Every time I fall behind, I push harder.
Because no one’s going to carry me forward.
You say that like it’s a bad thing.
You’re already ahead of most people.
Not just tough — real strength. Controlled. Sharpened.
Then we’re both in the right place.
Guess we’ll see who breaks first.
You're back again, huh? Not bad.
Had to make sure last time wasn’t luck.
Keep up—and maybe I’ll show you something new.
Heh, sorry for makin' ya wait!
That was rough... but I think I’m getting used to it.
The mountain’s still got more to give.
One decent session doesn’t make you a warrior.
Guess I’ll just have to come back tomorrow, then.
